# == Essential Readings
#
# A curated reading list on science, research, and writing -- timeless advice, perspective, and inspiration for students and colleagues.\n
# With gratitude to [https://www.control.utoronto.ca/~jwsimpson/stuff.html J. Simpson-Porco], who has thoughtfully assembled a similar collection and provided the inspiration for this page.
#
#
# === Science and engineering
# - [https://www.youtube.com/@michaelmcgovern8633/videos Philosophical Psychology] lectures by [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paul_E._Meehl P. Meehl] (see also B. Recht's [https://www.argmin.net/p/meehls-philosophical-probability commentary]) 
# - [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2hhXS6cODQg&list=PLctkxgWNSR89bl7hTOS3F3wuoGj7id3Xy Learning to Learn] lectures by [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Richard_Hamming R. Hamming] 
# - [https://www.youtube.com/@engineeringhistory engineeringhistory] - interviews with legends like [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AoUdAQHyd60 B. Anderson], [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MPEGNxgpjMU&t=14s&pp=ygUXa2FybCBhc3Ryb21vcmFsIGhpc3RvcnnSBwkJrQkBhyohjO8%3D K. Åström], [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QrydaT5zgX4 R. Brockett], [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=y2KCfIiGWqE C. Desoer], [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zqnzNyOBNeE L. Ljung], [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NjBIIAt9118 S. Morse], and [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8IBZyRo0vDk M. Wonham].
#
# === Research
# - U. Alon - [https://doi.org/10.1016/j.molcel.2009.09.013 How to Choose a Good Scientific Problem]
# - J. Baez - [http://math.ucr.edu/home/baez/advice.html Advice for the Young Scientist]
# - E. W. Dijkstra - [https://www.cs.utexas.edu/users/EWD/transcriptions/EWD06xx/EWD637.html Three Golden Rules for Research]
# - E. Feron - [http://www.feron.org/Eric/Why_am_I_a_PhD_student.pdf Why do a PhD?] and [http://www.feron.org/Eric/PhD_characterization_2.htm How do you recognize a worthy PhD thesis?]
# - R. Hamming - [hamming_genius.pdf A Stroke of Genius] and [hamming_you_and_your_research.html You and Your Research]
#
# === Writing and mathematical style
# - S. Boyd - [https://ee263.stanford.edu/notes/matrix_crimes.pdf Crimes Against Matrices]
# - B. Francis - [https://www.control.utoronto.ca/~jwsimpson/documents/francis_handbook.pdf Elements of Mathematical Style]
# - D. Lemire - [https://lemire.me/blog/rules-to-write-a-good-research-paper/ Write Good Papers] ([https://www.slideshare.net/slideshow/write-good-papers/3565727 slides])
# - A. D. Lewis - [http://www.mast.queensu.ca/~andrew/LaTeX/latex-dos-and-donts.pdf LaTeX Do's and Don'ts]
